------------------------------------------------------------------------

Upstream:    icloudza/algokiller-plugin, tools/search/search.c (Sprints 1-6)
Upstream license: MIT
Upstream copyright: Copyright (c) 2026 cloudza

The following Python modules in `engine/engine/` are ports of plugin-extension
code from search.c. Only the Sprint 1-6 plugin-extension subcommands (MIT) were
ported; the original `match` / `context` / `daemon` engine paths upstream of
that plugin (separately attributable to @lidongyooo) are NOT vendored.

  engine/data/fingerprints.py
    Port of:           static const Fingerprint FINGERPRINTS[]
                       static const InstructionPattern INSTR_PATTERNS[]
                       per_block_primitive_for()
                       Verdict enum
    From section:      Sprint 4 / constscan, search.c §2316-2750
    Reimplemented in:  Python dataclasses + Confidence enum
    Constants are RFC/FIPS/GM-standard values (MD5 init, SHA-256 K-table, etc).
    The compilation, taxonomy, and confidence ratings are ported verbatim.

  engine/fold.py
    Port of:           run_fold(), run_fold_block(), fold_flush_run(),
                       line_signature_hash()
    From section:      Sprint 2 / fold, search.c §1500-1651
    Adapted to operate on our Instruction stream rather than raw text lines.

  engine/dataflow.py
    Port of:           run_regflow(), run_producer(), classify_semop()
    From section:      Sprint 1 / regflow, producer, semop, search.c §920-1180
    Adapted to use pre-parsed regs_write/regs_read fields on Instruction.

We did NOT port or vendor:
  - tools/search/search.c match/context/daemon engine paths
    (upstream provenance: @lidongyooo / AlgoKiller, separate copyright)
  - The ak_search binary, Makefile, build.sh
  - The MCP server, Skills, agents, hooks, commands directories
  - Anything from the .claude-plugin/ namespace

